{
  "text": "A fourth source of dendritic [Ca 2+ ] i increase are NMDA spikes (Schiller et al. 2000; [CITATION_1] . These large, spatially restricted [Ca 2+ ] i increases result from the regenerative activation of NMDA receptors and dendritic Ca 2+ channels and have been shown to affect LTP in certain regions of pyramidal cell basal dendrites [CITATION_2] ).",
  "correct_citation": {
